1.title: Episode 0: Healing Factors
1.plot: Which has the cooler healing factors, those found in nature or those found in pop culture? Kyle is all in on the axolotl salamander while Dan is championing the merc with a mouth Deadpool. But which one will be naturally selected?

2.title: Dinosaurs vs. Dragons
2.plot: In a high-flying throw down of prehistoric proportions, it's a battle between dinosaurs and dragons. Kyle is rooting for the real-life T-Rex while Dan is on the Smaug pop culture express. But who will be naturally selected? Join host Dani Fernandez, guest judge Ify Nwadiwe, and the Alpha community to find out.

3.title: House Cats vs. Thundercats
3.plot: Thunder, thunder, Thundercats or house cats? This battle between a beloved cartoon series and our feline animal companions will come to an end as Dan and Kyle try to sway host Dani Fernandez, guest judge Joan Ford, and the Alpha community to their side. Which will be naturally selected?

4.title: Wizards vs. Scientists
4.plot: A thematic debate show featuring Dan Cave's Dan Casey on the side of pop culture and Because Science's Kyle Hill on the side of real life. Each will argue for their chosen side (e.g., Spider-Man vs. Spiders) and the audience will choose the winner.

5.title: Westworld vs. Boston Dynamics
5.plot: Which is cooler: Westworld or Boston Dynamics? We'll finally settle this debate as Kyle goes in for the real world Atlas robot while Dan saddles up with Dolores Abernathy. Who will be naturally selected? Your host Dani Fernandez, guest judge Jackie Kashian, and the Alpha community will decide.

6.title: Ant-Man vs. Wasps
6.plot: Does Ant-Man pack enough of a punch to be cooler than wasps? We'll finally settle this insect debate once and for all as Kyle uses all the terrifying wasp facts he can find. And guest pop culture expert Hector Navarro jumps to the Quantum Realm to fight on team Ant-Man.

7.title: Pokémon Evolution vs. Human Evolution Live from SDCC!
7.plot: Which is cooler: Pokémon evolution or evolutions found in humans? Gather your gym badges and brush up on your type weaknesses, cause this argument will be solved once and for all. Host Dani Fernandez, guest judge Jessica Chobot, and the Alpha community will vote to decide the winner, live from the Nerdist House at SDCC.
